{"timestamp":"2025-11-08T15:51:36.093Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"- `useDebounce` returns a value that only updates after the source value stays unchanged for the delay (600 ms here). So every keystroke immediately updates `filter.searchTerm`, but `debouncedSearchTerm` lags until typing pauses.\n- React Query creates its parameters, cache key, and `enabled` flag from that debounced value. While a user is typing quickly, `debouncedSearchTerm` doesn’t change; the hook sees the same key and disabled state, so it doesn’t issue new network calls.\n- Once the user stops typing for ≥600 ms, `useDebounce` publishes the latest term. The `useQuery` hook reruns with the new key and `enabled: true`, triggering exactly one fetch for that settled term."}}
